text: Germán Suárez Flamerich (10 April 1907 – 24 June 1990) was the President of Venezuela from 1950 to 1952. Suárez was a lawyer, college professor, diplomat, and politician. He was president of the Government Junta from 1950 to 1952, after the assassination of Carlos Delgado Chalbaud. Category:1907 births Category:1990 deaths Category:Presidents of Venezuela
